
<p>Lord, have mercy.<br/><i>Christ, have mercy.</i><br/>Lord, have mercy.</p>
<p><i>At Ordinations, the Bishop who is presiding stands and says</i></p>
<p>The Lord be with you.</p>
<p><i>People</i>  And also with you.</p>
<p><i>Bishop</i>  Let us pray.</p>
<p>The Bishop says the appointed Collect.</p>
<p><i>When this Litany is used on other occasions, the Officiant concludes<br/>with a suitable Collect.</i></p>
    